The credentials were always being fetched, even when not uploading
artifacts. The problem is that the Artifactory credentials are not
attached in all steps where Gradle is called.

This solution just sets the Artifactory credentials if an upload
is going to happen.

Without this teams will be blind about what is the issue. It can be that the credentials are not attached, it can be that the credential name is wrong, it can be an issue with ectool. Let the exception be raised and fixed by the teams.

There is a bug with compiled Groovy code on JDK6 when it runs on Java 8:
Caused by: java.lang.IncompatibleClassChangeError: the number of constructors during runtime and compile time for java.lang.RuntimeException do not match. Expected 4 but got 5

More information:
